de.unlixx.runpng.util.undo

Class Undoable<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.unlixx.runpng.util.undo.Undoable<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The source class type.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    UndoableCollection, UndoableIntegerSpinner, UndoableTextInput, UndoableToggleGroup

    public abstract class Undoable<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    An abstract Undoable class. Implementors need to add a void undoAction() and a void redoAction() to complete the class instantiation.

      • setRunFinally

        public void setRunFinally(java.lang.Runnable runFinally)
        Set a Runnable which will be invoked after each undo or redo. This strategy can be used if an override of runFinally() makes no sense at the point of Undoable creation.
        Parameters:
        runFinally - The runnable to invoke.
